":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: status name, occupational name, or a nickname from Middle English <i>squyer</i>, <i>squer</i>, <i>skier</i>, <i>sker</i>, northern Middle English <i>swire</i> (Old French <i>escuyer</i>, <i>escuier</i>) ‘shield bearer, esquire, personal attendant to a knight; landowner below the rank of knight; young man of gentle birth; household attendant, retainer, page, messenger’. Many early bearers of this name were of modest means and cannot have been members of the gentry; in such cases the name may have been used hyperbolically for a low-ranking servant or as a nickname. By the 17th century, the term denoted any member of the landed gentry, but this is unlikely to have influenced the development of the surname."],"variants":[{"name":"Swire","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): variant of   Squire  , from a northern form of the word."]},{"name":"Quire","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Squire  .","Scottish or Irish: shortened form of   McQuire   (see   McGuire  )."]},{"name":"Squires","meanings":["English: variant of   Squire  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Scuderi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carmelo, Salvatore, Angelo, Carlo, Gaetano, Vito, Antonio, Dante, Mario, Rocco, Rosario, Antonino, Biaggio, Eduardo, Ermelinda, Margarita.","Italian (Sicily): status name equivalent to   Squire  , from <i>scudiero</i>, <i>scutiero</i>, dialect <i>scuteri</i> ‘shieldbearer’ (from medieval Latin <i>scutarius</i>, an agent derivative of <i>scutum</i> ‘shield’). In Byzantium, the Greek word <i>skoutarios</i> denoted a member of the imperial guard."]},{"name":"Square","meanings":["English (Devon) and Scottish (Lanarkshire): variant of   Squire  ."]},{"name":"Squier","meanings":["English: variant of   Squire  ."]}]},{"name":"Deol","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Dion ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":20,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Deol Squire was born in 1435, in Hampshire, England. She had at least 2 sons with Thomas Squyre. She died in 1458, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1435–1458":"1435–1458","1430–1505":"1430–1505","1450–1481":"1450–1481","1458–1528":"1458–1528","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1481":"1481","1528":"1528","1505":"1505","Romsley, Worcestershire, England":"Romsley, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Benwick, Cambridgeshire, England":"Benwick, Cambridgeshire, England"},"fi":{"1435–1458":"1435–1458","1430–1505":"1430–1505","1450–1481":"1450–1481","1458–1528":"1458–1528","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1481":"1481","1528":"1528","1505":"1505","Romsley, Worcestershire, England":"Romsley, Worcestershire, England","Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Benwick, Cambridgeshire, England":"Benwick, Cambridgeshire, England"},"fr":{"1435–1458":"1435–1458","1430–1505":"1430–1505","1450–1481":"1450–1481","1458–1528":"1458–1528","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1450":"1450","1481":"1481","1528":"1528","1505":"1505","Romsley, Worcestershire, England":"Romsley, Worcestershire, Angleterre","Hampshire, England":"Hampshi